				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: I wonder when Everquest will be abandonware<a name="67265"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 18 04 2:09 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;That is, if EQ2 is as cool as folks say it is. &quot;
<br />

<br />
I must admit that the feedback I have seen has been uniformly lukewarm.   Lot's of beta testers saying they still do not know if they will switch.     The only consistent positive opinion is of the graphics.   
<br />

<br />
Many if not most hardcore EQ'ers switch off all the new graphics, disable spell effects and do everything they can to make sure performance is up to the absolute max.   Content &gt; Graphics by a massive margin.   So saying it is graphically impressive, doesnt impress me.
<br />

<br />
Things that put me off are:
<br />

<br />
- no pulling, every multi mob encounter is a zerg
<br />
- the new KS rules
<br />
- no bards
<br />
- saying bye bye to a toon that I have been playing for nearly 4 years
<br />
- no helping people (some would call this PL'ing) but I have often seen someone gettin into trouble, mezzed the mob, used AE song to heal, slowed mob and babysat them thru the kill.  Helping others = good.
<br />
- Will everyone i know move? I know loads of people in game, I like it that way
<br />

<br />
etc etc
<br />

<br />
If EQ1 dies, I will quit with it, I'm not going through this again
<br />

<br />
Melo
<br />
