				<td colspan="2"><span>Let me start by saying that I am fairly new to EQ, but not the MMORPG world.
<br />

<br />
I dont see EQ dying anytime in the near future.  EQII wont kill it, WoW wont do it, and i honestly cant think of a scenario where a single game will put EQ under.  EQ is too deep and rich of a game to just disapear.  I hear plenty of people talking about all the different games they want to play, but none of those games can hold a candle to the size and complexity of EQ.  How can you expect a game to just show up with 6+ years worth of work already in it.  The Everquest community doesnt know how good it has it.  Also do you expect some of the people who have put 3 and 4 YEARS worth of work into an account to just let it go?  Thats saying nothing of the community.  I have hardly been playing a month and a half and i already have friends and people i would happily help out.  People arent going to leave behind friendships they have cultivated for so long.
<br />

<br />
Also along a slightly different veign, I dont fully understand all the complaining that goes on in EQ forums in general (not this one specifically).  Perhaps when im a lvl 70 with max AA's i will understand better.  This is a GAME.  I play to have fun, talk with people, and get my blood pumping.  There is nothing quite like doing CC or pulling for a group.  If at any time the game stops being fun, and becomes something i worry and complain about ill leave that same day.  Maybe im being a bit harsh, but i think one of the reasons EQ is having difficulty is because everyone on various boards being so negative all the time.  If there wasnt an overwhelming sense of distress perhaps it would draw more people.
<br />

<br />
Back to the origional point, i dont honestly see EQ shutting down the servers for another 5 or 6 years minimum.
<br />

